procstep.procdesc: FREAC updated their PLSS layer in 1999. In January 2000, SJRWMD GIS Division staff obtained a copy and revised the attribute tables by replacing the major/minor pairs with new item names. FREAC changed the code for many polygons previously coded as 199 (unsurveyed - a code no longer used) or 198 (water - as in some lake polygons) to 110. Additionally, several river/stream systems were open to the universe polygon and therefore uncoded. GIS Division staff added closure arcs; the resulting polygon was attributed in the exception and comment items of the .pat, and the closure arcs were noted in the .aat. Original data was not altered; exceptions were noted with comments. Additionally, September 2001, Sections with numbers greater than 36 with Township and Range = 0 were populated with the proper Township and Range data by staff in the Division of Integrated Application Systems.

Dec. 2002, GIS staff updated the structure of attribute table. This update is only for the PLSS AOI button to work. The reason to update is that users find that the SECTION number of this layer do not always match the Identification number in the DRG 24K map. Later research also found that the NONSEC_ID value matches the identification number in the DRG 24k Map in most cases.
Two new fields were added. STR_OLD keeps the origin old value of STR, which equal to SEC&TOWN&RNG. SEC2 value is based on field SEC, but for those records with NONSEC_ID value, their SEC2 value are set to NONSEC_ID value. STR field value were updated for any records with duplicated STR_OLD value and with non_0 NONSEC_ID value. Their STR value are set to SEC2&TOWN&RNG, for all the other records, the STR value = STR_OLD value.

edom.edomvd: x = 0 for numeric section identifier; 1 for numeric part of alphanumeric section identifier; 2 for alphabetic part of alphanumeric section identifier yyy = Section number, flush right, or numeric code for alphabetic character, flush right: A = 01, B = 02, C= 03, D= 04, E = 05, F = 06, G= 07, H = 08, I = 09, J = 10, K = 11, L = 12, M = 13, N = 14, O = 15, P = 16, Q = 17, R = 18, S = 19, T = 20, U = 21, V = 22, W = 23, X = 24, Y = 25, Z = 26 Examples: Section 36 = 0036; Section 101 = 0101; Section 23A = 1023, 2001. NOTE: Sections greater than 36 are land grant areas.

x = 0 for full township; 2 for 1/4 township; 4 for 1/2 township; 6 for 3/4 township. yyyy = township number, flush right. xyyy = North of Baseline -xyyy = South of Baseline. Examples: Township 101 South = -0101; Township 23 1/2/ North = 4023

x = 0 for full range; 2 for 1/4 range; 4 for 1/2 range; 6 for 3/4 range; 8 for duplicate to north or east of the original township; 9 for triplicate to north or east of a duplicate township. yyy = range number, flush right. xyyy = East of Principal Meridian. -xyyy = West of Principal Meridian. Examples: Range 5 East = 0005e; Range 47 West, duplicate to north or east of the original township = 8047. EXCEPTION X: 0 = no exceptions to data as received from FREAC 1 = exception to data or possible mis-code; data remains unchanged but additional information is noted in 'comment' item.
